      "side": 1,
      "message": "Just confirming my reading comprehension: once we call eglSetMaxGLESVersion for the first time, we haven\u0027t dispatched to the desktop GL yet. But when we call setMaxGlesVersion from here, it\u0027s either before the GLES1/2/3 contexts have populated their desktop GL dispatch tables, or they have already been populated so it\u0027s a no-op.\n\nIf the former case, then the GLES1/2/3 contexts will avoid filling in the GLES3 entries if GLES3 is disabled.\n\nIf the latter case, then we assume that the first context to do any GL ops is a context that achieves the max GLES version wanted (c.f. the FrameBuffer.cpp changes) so we are still good.\n\nDoes this sound right?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1562,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 1562,
        "endChar": 66
      },
